From 1bf133d60db0016099b73dd45e49da8bd11f5316 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: eunseobchoi <eunseobchoi@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 08:02:18 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] Reject malformed UTXO transfer fields before state changes

Malformed JSON field types reached string normalization and output box derivation before validation, so public transfer requests could return 500s and malformed mempool candidates could remain unmineable until expiry. Validate JSON root shape, required text field types, and UTXO output addresses at both endpoint and state-transition boundaries.

Constraint: RustChain UTXO bounty #2819 rewards practical hardening around mempool DoS, unchecked error paths, and missing validations
Rejected: Only catch AttributeError in /utxo/transfer | leaves malformed output candidates accepted below the endpoint layer
Confidence: high
Scope-risk: narrow
Directive: Keep mempool output validation aligned with apply_transaction so unmineable candidates cannot lock UTXOs
Tested: uv run --no-project --with pytest --with flask python -m pytest node/test_utxo_db.py node/test_utxo_endpoints.py -q
Tested: python3 -m py_compile node/utxo_db.py node/utxo_endpoints.py node/test_utxo_db.py node/test_utxo_endpoints.py
Tested: git diff --check
Not-tested: Full repository suite; legacy node/test_utxo_empty_outputs_bug.py still omits _allow_minting for mining_reward setup and fails before its intended assertion
